90 Evo hero box shot\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/03/samsung-990-evo-ssd-hero-box.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/03/samsung-990-evo-ssd-hero-box.jpg\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\n\n        \n                    \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan data-field=\"label\"\u003eRelated\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\n\n                \n                 \n                \t\n\u003ch5\u003e\n\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t        \t\t\t\t\n\t\t\u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/samsung-990-evo-review/\" title=\"Samsung 990 Evo 2TB review: A bewildering launch for a lackluster SSD\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\n\t\t\tSamsung 990 Evo 2TB review: A bewildering launch for a lackluster SSD\n\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\u003c/h5\u003e\n\n                                                    \n                \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003eSamsung\u0026#39;s latest mainstream desktop and laptop M.2 NVMe SSD is a decent enough drive for the right price. \u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\n\n                    \n\n\n                \n                \n                \n                \n\n                \n                \n                \n                \t\n\n\n                \n\n                \n                \n                \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n                \n        \n        \n        \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"what-39-s-great-about-samsung-39-s-990-evo-ssd\"\u003e\n                        What\u0026#39;s great about Samsung\u0026#39;s 990 Evo SSD?\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n    \n\n\n\n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                \n    \n\n\u003cp\u003eFor the most part, you\u0026#39;re getting excellent bang for your buck at this price. With the SSD providing reasonable performance, with sequential read speeds that top out at 5,000 MB/s, and sequential write speeds that max out at 4,200 MB/s. It\u0026#39;s great for daily use and the perfect upgrade for most desktops and laptops. \u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eHowever, if you\u0026#39;re thinking about popping this into a gaming PC, it can be done, but we wouldn\u0026#39;t recommend it since it doesn\u0026#39;t have DRAM. If playing games is your sole intention, than we recommend going with other \u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/best-m-2-ssd/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eM.2 SSD options\u003c/a\u003e if your budget allows it. What makes this SSD a little different from others is its compatibility with PCIe 4.0 x4 and PCIe 5.0 x2. \u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eAnd while the Gen5 performance isn\u0026#39;t the best, it\u0026#39;s an option. But for the most part, we recommend using this as a Gen4 drive. Of course, since this is a Samsung SSD, you\u0026#39;re going to get excellent reliability, with the drive rated to handle up to 600 TBW (terabytes written). In addition, Samsung also provides a five-year warranty.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eAgain, what really pushes this SSD over the top is the price. At $65, it\u0026#39;s pretty good purchase. So grab it while you can. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003c/div\u003e\n    \n                \n        \n        \n\n\n        \n\n\n\n\n\n                \n    \u003c/article\u003e\n\n    \n            \n        \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
